headline: UPDATE 4-Visa gets vaccine boost as domestic spending back near pre-COVID levels
summary: Visa Inc beat estimates for quarterly profit on Tuesday, with domestic spending almost back to pre-pandemic levels and international travel on the road to recovery as rising vaccinations and reopening economies take effect.  Visa reported a 34% jump in third-quarter payment volumes on a constant dollar basis, while the number of transactions processed surged 39%.  "In our domestic businesses, we are pretty much back to where we were, had the pandemic never happened," Chief Financial Officer Vasant Prabhu told Reuters.
